# Chapter 9: Clustering

## Introduction

Clustering is an Unsupervised Machine Learning technique used to group similar data points together.

Unlike supervised learning, clustering does not require labeled data.

The algorithm automatically discovers hidden patterns and structures within the dataset.

---

# What is Clustering?

Clustering divides data into groups called clusters.

Data points within the same cluster are more similar to each other than to data points in other clusters.

